                        <h2>Proper Nutrition for Dogs</h2>
                        <img src="imgs/eating.png" alt="" class="d-none d-lg-inline">
                        <p class="lead">A crucial aspect of dog pet care is ensuring they receive proper nutrition.
                            Providing a balanced and nutritious diet is
                            essential for their overall health and well-being. Dogs require a diet that includes
                            high-quality protein, essential
                            fatty acids, carbohydrates, vitamins, and minerals. Consult with a veterinarian to determine
                            the best diet for your dog
                            based on factors like age, breed, size, and any specific dietary requirements or
                            restrictions. Feed them regular meals
                            at consistent times, avoid overfeeding, and provide access to fresh water at all times.
                            Remember to offer healthy treats
                            in moderation and avoid feeding them foods that are toxic or harmful to dogs.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row align-items-center content">
