                        <h2>Exercise and Physical Activity</h2>
                        <img src="imgs/dogrun1.png" alt="" class="d-none d-lg-inline">
                        <p class="lead">Regular exercise is vital for maintaining a dog's physical and mental health.
                            Different breeds have varying exercise
                            needs, so it's important to understand your dog's requirements. Engage them in daily
                            activities like walks, runs, play
                            sessions, and interactive games. Exercise not only helps keep them fit but also provides
                            mental stimulation, reduces
                            behavioral issues, and strengthens the bond between you and your dog. Consider the size,
                            age, and energy level of your
                            dog when planning exercise routines. If you have any concerns or limitations regarding
                            exercise, consult with your
                            veterinarian for appropriate guidance.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
