            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 text-center order-1 order-md-2">
                <div class="row justify-content-center">
                    <div class="col-10 col-lg-8 blurb mb-5 mb-md-0">
                        <h2>Grooming and Hygiene</h2>
                        <img src="imgs/hi.png" alt="" class="d-none d-lg-inline">
                        <p class="lead">Proper grooming and hygiene are essential for keeping your dog healthy and
                            comfortable. Regular brushing helps maintain
                            a clean and tangle-free coat, removes loose hair, and distributes natural oils. The
                            frequency of grooming depends on the
                            breed and coat type. Additionally, regular nail trimming, dental care, and ear cleaning are
                            important aspects of pet
                            care. Keep an eye out for any signs of skin issues, parasites, or abnormalities and consult
                            your veterinarian if you
                            notice anything concerning. Finally, provide a clean and safe environment for your dog,
                            ensuring their living space is
                            regularly cleaned and sanitized to prevent the spread of germs and infections.

                            These three paragraphs highlight different aspects of dog pet care: nutrition, exercise, and
                            grooming/hygiene. Each
                            paragraph focuses on a specific topic, providing key information and emphasizing the
                            importance of these aspects in
                            maintaining the health and well-being of dogs.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
